--- /home/packages/ptpd-2.2.0/README	2012-02-01 11:22:49.000000000 -0500
+++ ./README	2015-10-26 22:23:26.676556000 -0400
@@ -22,6 +22,35 @@
 probably want something that implements the Network Time Protocol. It can
 coordinate computer clocks with an absolute time reference such as UTC.
 
+- Build release tarball -
+  $TILERA_ROOT/src/ptpd-2.2.0.get
+  cd ptpd-2.2.0
+  make
+
+- Native Build -
+  Copy the release tarball 'ptpd-2.2.0.tar.gz' generated by last step from
+  $TILERA_ROOT/src/ptpd-2.2.0/ to a native machine, then run
+
+  tar xzvpf ptpd-2.2.0.tar.gz
+  cd ptpd-2.2.0
+  make -C src
+
+- Install -
+  make -C src install
+
+- Demo -
+To sync the slave's time up with the master's time,
+On Master run:
+  ptpd2 -c -d -W
+
+On Slave run:
+  ptpd2 -c -d -g
+
+- Cross Build -
+  export CC=$TILERA_ROOT/bin/tile-gcc
+  make -C src
+  make -C src install BASEDIR=$TILERA_ROOT/tile
+
 - Legal notice -
 
 PTPd was written by using only information contained within 'IEEE Std
